==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[calculare#Latin|calculare]]''

===Transitive verb===
'''to calculate''' ('''calculates''', '''calculating''', '''calculated''')

#<!--DefA-->{{mathematics}} To determine the value of something or the solution to something by a mathematical process.
#:''Calculate the square root of 3 to 10 decimal places.''

====Synonyms====
*<!--DefA-->(''determine value of or solution to''): [[compute]], [[reckon]] (''old''), [[work out]]

====Translations====
'''to determine value''
{{top}}
*Dutch: [[berekenen]], [[uitwerken]]
*Finnish: [[laskea]]
*Français: [[calculer]]
*German: [[berechnen]], [[ausrechnen]]
*Japanese: [[計算]]する (けいさんする,keisansuru)
{{mid}}
*Polish: [[wyliczać]], [[kalkulować]]
*Russian: [[вычислять]], [[считать]], [[подсчитывать]]
{{bottom}}

===Intransitive verb===
'''to calculate''' ('''calculates''', '''calculating''', '''calculated''')

#<!--DefB-->{{mathematics}} To determine values or solutions by a mathematical process.
#<!--DefC-->To [[plan]] something, especially something morally wrong.

====Synonyms====
*<!--DefB-->(''determine values or solutions''): [[compute]], [[reckon]] (''old'')
*<!--DefC-->(''plan''): [[plan]], [[plot]], [[scheme]]

